Fern Britton reveals how her depression led to a suicide attempt Fern Britton, the host of This Morning programme, has spoken of her fight with depression which led her to attempt suicide. Fern Britton said there had been days when she "could hardly get out of bed" Photo: SKY	By Urmee Khan 11:58AM GMT 27 Oct 2008
The television presenter revealed how she was so depressed that she planned to crash her car into a brick wallBritton, 51, said: "There were days I could hardly get out of bed. I was so seriously depressed I needed medication. It was very tough. "If I wasn't such a coward, I know I would have killed myself. I contemplated it very seriously. I remember sitting in the bath one day thinking 'How many pills have I got in the bottle?'" she said."I did seriously think about driving the car into a brick wall. It was that bad. I remember writing a letter, not a suicide note, but a letter to myself to read the next day when I was feeling better to see if it made me think, 'Pull yourself together'. But it didn't. It made me cry. I didn't know what to do."The mother of four, describes the experiences in a her forthcoming memoir, 'My Life by Fern Britton'.
