Britton said Phil Vickery, the chef, had been her salvation since they met on her show Ready Steady Cook. She said: "I was halfway to falling apart. If it hadn't been for Phil, God knows what would have happened. I think I would have done myself in. Phil was the only person who knew how serious it was. He helped to pull me through." The host of ITV1's This Morning said her husband had been a pillar of strength during the controversy over her gastric band operation in May. She was accused of deceiving people by failing to mention the band and suggesting that her weight loss was down to healthy eating and exercise. She subsequently had time off for stress. "I did it for me because I wanted to. I didn't feel I had to ring round and let everyone know", she said. Celebrity news
