Battle Of Marengo, second in the King Edward VII Stakes at Royal Ascot after finishing fourth at Epsom, is reopposed by Derby fifth Ocovango. As only half-a-length separated the pair at Epsom, I fancy the Andre Fabre-trained colt to get back on the winning list.
Brian Toomey, the jump jockey who suffered a severe head injury at Perth last week, has made some slight improvement, according to a report issued by the Injured Jockeys Fund on Friday.
Although he remains in intensive care, he is no longer under sedation and his condition has not deteriorated. There have been signs of movement, although he remains on a ventilator to assist his breathing. Close friends are welcome to visit, according to the statement.
